{
  "texts": [
    "There were no frames with exceptional patient preparation or poor visibility quality as a result of visual blurring that was discarded.",
    "Therefore, 31 frame sequences consisting of an average of 25 frames were created, with a special emphasis on obtaining as many polyp appearances as possible.",
    "The CVC-ClinicDB database contains 612 images of polyps with an overall size of 576 × 768.",
    "Ma et al. (2021) represent 612 images with a resolution of 384 × 288 with 29 videos on polyps.",
    "Park and Lee (2022) show that the training dataset contains 550 images and the testing dataset contains 62 images from the CVC ClinicDB with a resolution of 384 × 384 pixels."
  ]
}